{"lemma":"ذَهَبُ","slug":"ذَهَبُ","root":"ذ.ه.ب","root_slug":"ذ-ه-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ذ-ه-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"ذَهَب","root":"ذهب","pos":"N","occurrence_count":8},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":14},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n14112","","n14114","n14115","n14116"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B0%D9%8E%D9%87%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to go, to travel","examples":[{"text":"إِلَى أَيْنَ أَنْتَ ذَاهِبٌ؟","english":"Where are you going?"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to go away, to leave, to depart"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to disappear, to vanish"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to decline, to dwindle"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to perish, to die, to be destroyed"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to abduct, to steal, to sweep away, to annihilate"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to lead someone, to conduct someone, to take someone along"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to think, to believe, to hold the view, to be of the opinion","examples":[{"text":"فأمّا الْبَرِيد ففيه خلاف وذهب قوم إلى أنه بالبادية اثنا عشر ميلا وبالشام وخراسان ستة أميال","english":"About the postal route there is disagreement. Folks believed that in the desert it is twelve miles and in Syria and Khorasan six miles."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to escape, to slip, to lose sight of, to be forgotten"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to ignore, to skip, to omit"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to prepare to, to be about to"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to gild"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"gold","tags":["uncountable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"gold coin","tags":["uncountable"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"ذَهَبَ\nA Central Semitic innovation. Cognate with Hebrew זָהָב (zāhāḇ), Classical Syriac ܕܗܒܐ (dahbā), Old South Arabian 𐩹𐩠𐩨 (ḏhb)."},"ipa":["/ða.ha.ba/","/ðah.ha.ba/","/ða.hab/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n14112","headword_ar":"ذَهَبَ","root":"*hb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, &c.,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahaAbN","text_ar":"ذَهَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ihaAbN","text_ar":"ذِهَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uhuwbN","text_ar":"ذُهُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma*ohabN","text_ar":"مَذْهَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man, S, [and a beast,])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"went"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in any manner,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any pace"},{"kind":"text","text":"];"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"went,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"passed, along; marched; journeyed; proceeded: went,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"passed, away; departed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$aY","text_ar":"مَشَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAra","text_ar":"سَارَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mar~","text_ar":"مَرّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, A, K:) and said of a mark or trace or the like [as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it went away"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb.) [And hence, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It wasted away; became consumed, destroyed, exhausted, spent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"expended."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahaba A_ilayohi","text_ar":"ذَهَبَ اـِلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He went, repaired, betook himself,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"had recourse, to him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And they say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahaba Al$~aA^oma","text_ar":"ذَهَبَ الشَّاْمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He went to Syria"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; making the verb trans. without a particle; for although"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$A^m","text_ar":"الشام"},{"kind":"text","text":"is here a special adv. n., they liken it to a vague locality. (TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahaba Eanohu","text_ar":"ذَهَبَ عَنْهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, went from, quitted, relinquished,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"left, him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahaba fiYAlA^aroDi","text_ar":"ذَهَبَ فِىالاَرْضِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahaAbN","text_ar":"ذَهَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uhuwbN","text_ar":"ذُهُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma*ohabN","text_ar":"مَذْهَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He went away"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"into the country,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the land"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Msb:) [but it often means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he went into the open country,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"out of doors, to satisfy a want of nature:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or simply] (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he voided his excrement,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ordure."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahaba bihi","text_ar":"ذَهَبَ بِهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He went,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"went away, with him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he made him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, to go, go away, pass away,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"depart;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, Msb, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A*hbhu","text_ar":"اذهبهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, Msb, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bihi","text_ar":"بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A*hb","text_ar":"اذهب","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) but this is rare; (Zj, TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*h~bhu","text_ar":"ذهّبهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ta*ohiybN","text_ar":"تَذْهِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (MF:) [all may likewise be rendered"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he removed, dispelled, put away,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"banished, it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"properly and tropically: and (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he made it to cease; made away with it, did away with it, made an end of it; wasted, consumed, destroyed, exhausted, spent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"expended, it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and these meanings may perhaps be intended by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^azaAlahu","text_ar":"اَزَالَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", whereby the first is explained in the A and K, as are also the second and third in the K:] or, accord. to some, when"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahaba","text_ar":"ذَهَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is trans. by means of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bi","text_ar":"بِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", accompaniment is necessarily signified; but not otherwise; so that if you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahaba bihi","text_ar":"ذَهَبَ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the meaning is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he went away with him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"accompanying him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he took away,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"carried off"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"away, him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] but if you say ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A*hbhu","text_ar":"اذهبهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*h~bhu","text_ar":"ذهّبهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", the meaning is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he made him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, to go, go away, pass away,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"depart, alone, without accompanying him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"this, however, is not agreeable with the phrase in the Kur [ii. 16],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahaba A@ll~`hu binuwrihimo","text_ar":"ذَهَبَ ا@للّٰهُ بِنُورِهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[though this may be well rendered"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God taketh away their light"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (MF, TA.) [Hence,] one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ayona","text_ar":"اَيْنَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yu*ohabu bika","text_ar":"يُذْهَبُ بِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which may mean (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Where,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whither, wilt thou be taken away, and what will be done with thee and made to come to pass with thee,"},{"kind":"text","text":"if this be thine intellect? or, accord. to Mtr, it is a saying of the people of Baghdád, addressed to him whom they charge with foolish judgment or opinion, as meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ayona yu*ohabu biEaqolika","text_ar":"اَيْنَ يُذْهَبُ بِعَقْلِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Where,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whither, is thine intellect taken away?"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Har p. 574.) [In like manner one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahaba Eaqoluhu","text_ar":"ذَهَبَ عَقْلُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His reason,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intellect, quitted him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forsook him; he became bereft of his reason,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intellect."},{"kind":"text","text":"And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahaba fuw^aAduhu","text_ar":"ذَهَبَ فُوَادُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His heart forsook him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"failed him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"by reason of fear or the like.] And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahaba laHomuhu","text_ar":"ذَهَبَ لَحْمُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His flesh wasted away"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bHr","text_ar":"بحر"},{"kind":"text","text":", &c.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahaba Alr~ajulu fiY Alqawomi","text_ar":"ذَهَبَ الرَّجُلُ فِى القَوْمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The man became lost"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he disappeared"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"among the people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"party."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahaba AlmaA='a fiY All~abani","text_ar":"ذَهَبَ المَا=ءَ فِى اللَّبَنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The water became lost"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it disappeared"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the milk."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahaba Ealayohi","text_ar":"ذَهَبَ عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It escaped his memory; he forgot it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.) And (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, dubious, confused,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vague, to him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(MA.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahaba ma*ohabFA HasanFA","text_ar":"ذَهَبَ مَذْهَبًا حَسَنًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, TA) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He pursued a good way, course, mode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner, of acting"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conduct"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahaba fiY Ald~iyni ma*ohabFA","text_ar":"ذَهَبَ فِى الدِّينِ مَذْهَبًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He formed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"held, an opinion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a persuasion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a belief, respecting religion:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, accord. to Es-Sarakustee,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he introduced an innovation in religion."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahaba ma*ohaba fulaAnK","text_ar":"ذَهَبَ مَذْهَبَ فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He pursued the way, course, mode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner, of acting"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of such a one."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahaba li*ahobihi","text_ar":"ذَهَبَ لِذَهْبِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lima*ohabihi","text_ar":"لِمَذْهَبِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He pursued his way, course, mode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner, of acting"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. (JK, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahaba A_ilaY ma*ohabK","text_ar":"ذَهَبَ اـِلَى مَذْهَبٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He betook himself to"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"took to"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"held"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a belief, a creed, a persuasion, a doctrine, an opinion, a tenet,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a body of tenets"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"articles of belief."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN ya*ohabu","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ يَذْهَبُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilaY qawoli A^abiY Haniyfapa","text_ar":"اـِلَى قَوْلِ اَبِى حَنِيفَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one takes to,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"holds,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the saying,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the belief, creed, persuasion, doctrine,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of Aboo-Haneefeh."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) [And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahaba A_ilaY A^an~a AlA^amora ka*aA","text_ar":"ذَهَبَ اـِلَى اَنَّ الاَمْرَ كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He held,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was of opinion, that the thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"case, was so."},{"kind":"text","text":"And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahaba bilafoZK A_ilaYlafoZK A=xara","text_ar":"ذَهَبَ بِلَفْظٍ اـِلَىلَفْظٍ ا=خَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He regarded a word,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an expression,"},{"kind":"text","text":"in his manner of using it,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as equivalent to another word,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"expression;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as, for instance, when one makes a fem. noun masc. because it is syn. with a noun that is masc., or makes a verb trans. by means of a certain perticle because it is syn. with a verb that is trans. by means of that same particle: and also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he regarded a word,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an expression,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"etymologically relating,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"traceable, to another word,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"expression."},{"kind":"text","text":"And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahaba bihi A_ilaY maEonaY ka*aA","text_ar":"ذَهَبَ بِهِ اـِلَى مَعْنَى كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He regarded it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"used it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(i. e. a word, or an expression,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as relating to such a meaning,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as"},{"kind":"page_break","n":983},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"meaning such a thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahaba fiY Talabi Al$~aYo'i","text_ar":"ذَهَبَ فِى طَلَبِ الشَّىْءِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kul~a ma*ohabK","text_ar":"كُلَّ مَذْهَبٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He tried every way,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"did his utmost, in seeking the thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mwt","text_ar":"موت"},{"kind":"text","text":".) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahaba fiYAll~iyni kul~a ma*ohabK","text_ar":"ذَهَبَ فِىاللِّينِ كُلَّ مَذْهَبٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It attained the utmost degree of softness"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: said of the skin. (TA in that art.) ―         -b9-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ai*ohabo A_ilayoka","text_ar":"اِذْهَبْ اـِلَيْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Betake,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"apply, thyself to thine own affairs;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"occupy thyself therewith."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T and K * voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilaY","text_ar":"اـِلَى"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b10-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahaba A_ilaY A^abiyhi fiY Al$~abahi","text_ar":"ذَهَبَ اـِلَى اَبِيهِ فِى الشَّبَهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nazaEa","text_ar":"نَزَعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He inclined to his father in likeness; resembled him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"had a natural likeness to him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nzE","text_ar":"نزع"},{"kind":"text","text":".)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahiba","text_ar":"ذَهِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahabN","text_ar":"ذَهَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ihiba","text_ar":"ذِهِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with two kesrehs, (IAar, K,) of the dial. of Temeem, held by AM to be a variation generally allowable in the case of a verb of which the medial radical letter is a faucial and with kesr; (TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"saw gold in the mine,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"came suddenly, in the mine, upon much gold, and his reason departed in consequence thereof,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and his eyes became dazzled, so as not to close,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"move, the lids,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became confused, so as not to see,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by reason of the greatness thereof in his eye:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) it is derived from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahabN","text_ar":"ذَهَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and the epithet applied to a man in this case is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahibN","text_ar":"ذَهِبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["A","K","S","Msb","TA","MF","IAar"]},{"entry_id":"n14114","headword_ar":"ذَهْبٌ","root":"*hb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma*ohabN","text_ar":"مَذْهَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":       -A2-  and see also the last sentence of the paragraph here following."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n14115","headword_ar":"ذَهَبٌ","root":"*hb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Gold;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain thing well known;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, &c.;) accord. to several of the leading lexicologists, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tiborN","text_ar":"تِبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (A, L, K, &c.;) but it seems to have a more general meaning; for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tiborN","text_ar":"تِبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is specially applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gold"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as is in the mine,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as is uncoined and unwrought:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) [it is a coll. gen. n.; and therefore] it is masc. and fem.: (S, * Msb, K, * TA:) or it is fem. in the dial. of El-Hijáz: or, accord. to Az, it is masc., and not to be made fem. unless regarded as pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahabapN","text_ar":"ذَهَبَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, TA,) [or rather as a coll. gen. n., for]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahabapN","text_ar":"ذَهَبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the n. un., (K,) signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a piece of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahab","text_ar":"ذَهَب"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gold"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, A, L, TA:) or, accord. to El-Kurtubee, it is fem., and sometimes masc., but more commonly fem.: ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uhayobapN","text_ar":"ذُهَيْبَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the dim. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahabN","text_ar":"ذَهَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"being added because the latter word is fem., like as it is in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quwayosapN","text_ar":"قُوَيْسَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$umayosapN","text_ar":"شُمَيْسَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; or it is the dim. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahabapN","text_ar":"ذَهَبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a little piece of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahab","text_ar":"ذَهَب"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gold"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (TA:) the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahabN","text_ar":"ذَهَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a*ohaAbN","text_ar":"اَذْهَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a pl. of pauc.] (S, A, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uhuwbN","text_ar":"ذُهُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uhobaAnN","text_ar":"ذُهْبَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Nh, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ihobaAnN","text_ar":"ذِهْبَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Nh, TA.) ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA='u Al*~ahabi","text_ar":"مَا=ءُ الذَّهَبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Water-gold; goldpowder mixed with size, for ornamental writing &c."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b2-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"yolk,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"entire contents,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"yolk and white,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muH~","text_ar":"مُحّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", K, TA, with the unpointed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"H","text_ar":"ح"},{"kind":"text","text":", TA, [in the CK and in my MS. copy of the K"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mux~","text_ar":"مُخّ"},{"kind":"text","text":",])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of an egg."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)       -A2-  Also, (S, K,) in a copy of the T written ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahobN","text_ar":"ذَهْبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain measure of capacity, for corn, used by the people of ElYemen,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well known:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ihaAbN","text_ar":"ذِهَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a*ohaAbN","text_ar":"اَذْهَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [the latter a pl. of pauc.,] (S, K,) and pl. pl. [i. e. pl. of the latter of the pls. above]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a*aAhibu","text_ar":"اَذَاهِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, and so in the K accord. to the TA,) mentioned by A' Obeyd, (S,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a*aAhiybu","text_ar":"اَذَاهِيبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (So in the CK.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","Msb","K","S","A","L","Nh"]},{"entry_id":"n14116","headword_ar":"ذَهِبٌ","root":"*hb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see 1, last sentence."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}